Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "pristojan" in different forms and positions:

1. *Pristojan* čovek nikada ne bi rekao takve stvari. (A *decent* person would never say such things.)
2. Nadam se da ćemo pronaći *pristojno* mesto za večeru. (I hope we'll find a *nice* place for dinner.)
3. Moramo se *pristojno* obući za ovaj događaj. (We need to dress *appropriately* for this event.)
4. Ona je bila *pristojna* prema svima. (She was *polite* to everyone.)
5. *Pristojna* plata je važna za zadovoljstvo zaposlenih. (A *fair* salary is important for employee satisfaction.)
6. Većina ljudi bi se složila da je ova ponuda *pristojna*. (Most people would agree that this offer is *reasonable*.)
7. Ovaj hotel je veoma *pristojan* i udoban. (This hotel is very *decent* and comfortable.)

(Note: The word "pristojan" can be translated to various English words depending on the context, so the translations provided here are just one possible interpretation.)